{"name":"last-child","type":"selector","title":":last-child Selector","desc":"Selects all elements that are the last child of their parent.","categories":["selectors/child-filter-selectors","version/1.1.4"],"entries":[{"return":"","signatures":{"added":"1.1.4"},"examples":{"desc":"Find the last span in each matched div and add some css plus a hover state.","code":"\n$(\"div span:last-child\")\n    .css({color:\"red\", fontSize:\"80%\"})\n    .hover(function () {\n          $(this).addClass(\"solast\");\n        }, function () {\n          $(this).removeClass(\"solast\");\n        });\n","css":"\nspan.solast { text-decoration:line-through; }\n  ","html":"<div>\n    <span>John,</span>\n    <span>Karl,</span>\n    <span>Brandon,</span>\n    <span>Sam</span>\n  </div>\n  <div>\n    <span>Glen,</span>\n    <span>Tane,</span>\n\n    <span>Ralph,</span>\n    <span>David</span>\n  </div>"},"longdesc":"\n    <p>While <a href=\"/last-selector\">:last</a> matches only a single element, <code>:last-child</code> can match more than one: one for each parent.</p>\n  "}],"slug":"last-child-selector"}